<TITLE> Mohammedan to play against Sylhet, Tangail for Sidr survivors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com) - In a bid to raise the fund for Sidr survivors, Mohammedan Sporting Club will play two exhibition football matches against Sylhet and Tangail outside the capital. The first match will be played on November 30 against Sylhet DSA at the local stadium and the second one against Tangail DSA at its local stadium on December 1. "We stood by the victims of different disasters in the past, and we have come forward once again to stand by the Sidr victims in view of our own responsibility," Mohammedan SC additional general secretary Mustaqur Rahman said at a press conference on the premises Tuesday. "All money to be raised by the matches will go to the Chief Advisor's Relief Fund through the National Sports Council chairman and Army Chief General Moeen U Ahmed," said Rahman. Former star booter Rummon Bin Walid Sabbir will also play for Mohammedans against Sylhet while former defender Kaiser Hamid will also play for his old outfit against Tangail. Rahman hoped that the local spectators would come forward to help the Sidr survivors though watching the match as the tickets for galleries have been fixed for Tk 20 and the VIP for Tk 100. "We were also invited to play matches in Narsingdi, Netrokona, Mymensingh, Rajshahi and Patuakhali, and we have also decided to play those matches gradually after a three-match series against Abahani," said Rahman. Monir Ahmed, Mohammedan governing body member and Bangladesh Football Federation senior vice president, said the local administrations have taken initiatives through publicity. Coach Shafiqul Islam Manik said that Mohammedan full-strength team along with guest players Hasan Al Mamun, Arman Aziz, Aminul Islam, Rajani Kanta, Saikat, Mishu would play in both matches. Football committee secretary Nurunnabi, former footballers Kaiser Hamid, Sabbir, Imtiaz Sultan Jony and Imtiaz Ahmed Nakib were present among others. 
